  "description": [
    "ROOSEVELT SAYB Civil Rights Bill Will Become Law Continued from page 1 ca has a long way to go before it reaches the definition of what the word really means But the Congressman observed that as strange as it may seem to some of us many of the leaders in the fight for freedom over the years came from the south I Making a timely evaluation of the antiCivil Righters the Con gressman emphasized that those opposing Civil Rights just havent brought their thinking up to modern times The speaiker explained that many of those persons who brand organizations such as the NAAGP as extremists are themselves guilty of the same thing which they condemn Bringing the question right down to the State of Florida and other southern states the son of the late Preddent pointed out that several state legislatures have passed laws attacking and aimed at destroying the NAACP Os these efforts achieve their true ob jectives the 14th Amendment will be virtually appealed continued the speaker But I say to you therell be no appeal and these efforts will fail he added with much emphasis Touching Upon the question of Interposition the Congressman quoted from former President"
